294 Section 4. (a) Notwithstanding the provisions of Section
295 29-9-4, Code of Alabama 1975, and in addition to all other
296 appropriations heretofore or hereafter made, there is hereby
297 appropriated a total of $150,000,000 from the Education Trust
298 Fund Advancement and Technology Fund to the Department of
299 Education to provide matching grants to local education
300 agencies for expenses related to developing regional career
301 technology centers throughout the state, including capital
302 outlay and equipment, for the fiscal year ending September 30,
303 2026. Grant proposals shall be submitted by a collaboration of
304 at least two local education agencies or between a local
305 education agency partnering with a community college within
306 the Alabama Community College System. Should a local education
Page 12

the Alabama Community College System. Should a local education
HB236 Enrolled
307 agency partner with a community college, the local education
308 agency shall maintain full control of the grant from the
309 Department of Education.
310 (b) The State Superintendent of Education shall appoint a
311 committee to review and recommend grant proposals for
312 approval. The State Superintendent of Education shall utilize
313 a sliding scale of matching requirements for grant proposals,
314 taking into consideration the financial capacity of the
315 eligible local education agencies to provide matching funds,
316 so long as the required match does not exceed 50 percent of
317 the total cost of the project. The State Superintendent of
318 Education may give preference in awarding grants pursuant to
319 this section to grant proposals from local education agencies
320 that were not awarded the full amount of grant funds requested
321 pursuant to Act 2025-269, and to grant proposals from local
322 education agencies that submitted applications for grant funds
323 pursuant Act 2025-269 but did not receive a grant. However,
324 the total amount of grant funds that may be awarded for the
325 same project shall not exceed $20,000,000 for all grant years.
326 (c) The State Superintendent of Education shall notify
327 each local superintendent and finance officer of each local
328 education agency by email regarding the availability and
329 application process of grants to be awarded pursuant to this
330 section, including any required forms. The State
Page 13

section, including any required forms. The State
HB236 Enrolled
331 Superintendent shall notify all members of the local
332 legislative delegation five days prior to the announcement of
333 any grant made to any entity located in the legislative
334 jurisdiction. The five days prior notice requirement shall be
335 waived in the event of a declared emergency. The Governor
336 shall encourage the Department to disburse the funds provided
337 herein on a nondiscriminatory basis.
338 Section 5. All funds appropriated herein and not
339 expended in the current fiscal year shall not revert but be
340 carried forward for the purpose appropriated.
341 Section 6. This act shall become effective immediately
342 following its passage and approval by the Governor, or its
343 otherwise becoming law.
